cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper explores the gender distribution of roles in film and television, which can be seen as a social network. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing media databases and video content. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses mining information from media databases. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper explores the relationship between online and onscreen gender depictions. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper discusses methodologies that can be used by researchers to explore gender depictions in media.
